<paragraph blockId="3.[189,310,939,965]" box="[189,310,939,965]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,939,965]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,939,965]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,985,1082]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">A small dark brown species without fore femoral spines. The male genitalia are unique in having a greatly elongate sternite IX, with narrow V-shaped caudomedian cleft, and a Y-shaped aedeagus without ventral spicules and an abruptly tapered, sharply pointed apex. Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
