<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,768,900]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
The male antennal flagellum of this new species has an elongate flagellomere 10 and a bare aedeagus, characters typical of members of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1899" box="[737,814,804,829]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[737,814,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Bezzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This new species differs from all other Palearctic and Afrotropical members of the genus by its greatly elongate sternite IX, which extends to the midlength of the gonocoxites and covers their bases.
</paragraph>
